ct.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Fmusic%2Fnews%2Fdonna-summer-estate-kanye-west-ty-dolla-sign-lawsuit-1235924436%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Fmusic%2Fnews%2Fdonna-summer-estate-kanye-west-ty-dolla-sign-lawsuit-1235924436%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20former%20US%20surgeon%20general%20went%20to%20the%20ER%20for%20dehydration%20and%20ended%20up%20with%20a%20%245%2C000%20bill.%20He%20called%20healthcare%20a%20'broken%20system.'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222695%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20of%20Dr.%20Jerome%20Adams%2C%20the%20former%20US%20surgeon%20general%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ddf63f90413ab8e1d71372%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221466%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDr.%20Jerome%20Adams%2C%20the%20former%20US%20surgeon%20general%20in%20a%20suit%20and%20bowtie%3Cp%3EJohn%20Underwood%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFormer%20US%20Surgeon%20General%20Jerome%20Adams%20said%20he%20got%20a%20%245%2C000%20bill%20for%20a%20recent%20ER%20visit.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe's%20fighting%20the%20bill%2C%20which%20he%20said%20has%20been%C2%A0%26quot%3Bmentally%20taxing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHis%20experience%20highlights%20big%20problems%20with%20US%20healthcare%2C%20including%20high%20costs%20and%20no%20transparency.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20US%20surgeon%20general%20just%20got%20a%20taste%20of%20what's%20frustrated%20countless%20Americans%3A%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fdad-died-massive-medical-debt-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emassive%20medical%20bill%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Jerome%20Adams%2C%20who%20was%20the%20nation's%20top%20doctor%20from%202017%20to%202021%2C%20said%20he%20was%20slammed%20with%20an%20almost%20%245%2C000%20bill%20after%20being%20treated%20for%20dehydration%20at%20the%20Mayo%20Clinic's%20emergency%20department%2C%20where%20he%20got%20labs%20and%20a%20few%20IV%20bags.%20He%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FJeromeAdamsMD%2Fstatus%2F1761375417351430595%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshared%3C%2Fa%3E%20his%20experience%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%20in%20a%20post%20that%20went%20viral.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20Monday%20with%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Adams%20said%20he%20had%20gone%20to%20the%20ER%20in%20Scottsdale%2C%20Arizona%2C%20after%20he%20went%20hiking%20during%20a%20work%20trip%20in%20January%20and%20became%20lightheaded.%20Getting%20the%20big%20bill%20was%20shocking%E2%80%94even%20for%20a%20doctor%20well-acquainted%20with%20the%20pitfalls%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F30-leaders-under-40-changing-healthcare-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20healthcare%20system%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20said%20spending%20hours%20on%20the%20phone%20with%20hospital%20billing%20reps%20to%20get%20a%20clearer%20picture%20of%20why%20he%20was%20charged%20so%20much%20has%20been%20%26quot%3Bmentally%20taxing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Mayo%20Clinic%20did%20not%20immediately%20return%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdams%20said%20his%20experience%20highlights%20the%20exorbitant%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjama-study-on-us-healthcare-spending-compared-to-the-rest-of-the-world-2018-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecost%20of%20medical%20care%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhospital-price-transparency-rule-didnt-make-healthcare-shopping-easier-2021-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elack%20of%20price%20transparency%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Patients%20usually%20have%20no%20idea%20what%20a%20medical%20visit%20will%20cost%20ahead%20of%20time%2C%20and%20even%20if%20they%20did%2C%20it's%20impossible%20to%20shop%20around%20in%20an%20emergency.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20patients%20increasingly%20shoulder%20a%20larger%20portion%20of%20healthcare%20costs%20as%20insurance%20deductibles%20have%20crept%20higher.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdams%20said%20with%20all%20these%20obstacles%2C%20it's%20no%20wonder%20many%20Americans%20end%20up%20with%20medical%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I'm%20in%20this%20situation%20with%20my%20knowledge%20and%20with%20my%20financial%20resources%20and%20with%20my%20bully%20pulpit%2C%20then%20the%20average%20Joe%20doesn't%20stand%20a%20chance.%20The%20system%20is%20just%20broken%2C%26quot%3B%20Adams%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAdams'%20big%20medical%20bill%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fdoes-medical-debt-affect-credit-score%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMedical%20debt%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20widespread%20problem.%20An%20estimated%2020%20million%20people%20in%20the%20US%20owe%20medical%20debt%2C%20and%2014%20million%20people%20owe%20%241%2C000%20or%20more%2C%20according%20to%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.healthsystemtracker.org%2Fbrief%2Fthe-burden-of-medical-debt-in-the-united-states%2F%23Share%2520of%2520adults%2520who%2520have%2520medical%2520debt%2C%2520by%2520health%2520status%2520and%2520disability%2520status%2C%25202021%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Kaiser%20Family%20Foundation%20and%20the%20Peterson%20Center%20on%20Healthcare.%20Research%20has%20shown%20that%20medical%20debt%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC6366487%2F%23bib4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eleading%20cause%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20personal%20bankruptcy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20why%20Adams'%20bill%20was%20so%20high%20since%20he%20said%20he%20hasn't%20received%20a%20breakdown%20of%20the%20charges.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhealthcare-costs-lead-financial-worries-voting-presidential-election-biden-trump-2024-2%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOver%252070%2525%2520of%2520Democrats%252C%2520Republicans%2Cof%25205.5%2525%2520annually%2520through%25202031.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EER%20bills%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20notoriously%20expensive%20and%20can%20vary%20drastically%20from%20hospital%20to%20hospital.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdams%20said%20he%20was%20billed%20for%20a%20Level%205%20visit%2C%20which%20is%20a%20code%20used%20for%20patients%20with%20the%20highest%20level%20of%20severity%2C%20such%20as%20chest%20pain%20or%20stroke%20symptoms.%20The%20most%20complex%20cases%20fetch%20higher%20payments%20because%20they%20require%20more%20resources%20and%20time.%20But%20Adams%20is%20fighting%20the%20bill%20because%20he%20believes%20his%20visit%20should%20have%20been%20coded%20at%20a%20lower%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20issue%20is%20that%20Adams%20is%20enrolled%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-high-deductible-health-insurance-plans-dont-work-2018-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh-deductible%20health%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20requiring%20him%20to%20pay%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20out%20of%20pocket%20before%20he%20reaches%20the%20%26quot%3Bdeductible%26quot%3B%20and%20insurance%20starts%20picking%20up%20part%20of%20the%20tab.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHigh-deductible%20plans%20have%20become%20more%20common%20as%20employers%20have%20shifted%20the%20cost%20of%20medical%20care%20to%20their%20workers.%20The%20average%20annual%20deductible%20for%20individuals%20in%20one%20of%20these%20plans%20attached%20to%20a%20health-savings%20account%20was%20%242%2C518%20in%202023%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kff.org%2Freport-section%2Fehbs-2023-section-8-high-deductible-health-plans-with-savings-option%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKaiser%20Family%20Foundation%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Adams%20said%20his%20deductible%20is%20a%20whopping%20%247%2C500.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20health%20plans%20allow%20patients%20to%20put%20pre-tax%20money%20in%20a%20savings%20account%20each%20month%20to%20help%20them%20afford%20their%20medical%20bills.%20But%20since%20Adams'%20ER%20visit%20occurred%20in%20January%2C%20he%20hadn't%20built%20up%20any%20savings%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPatients%20need%20more%20clarity%20on%20big%20medical%20bills%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECongress%20has%20provided%20some%20relief%20from%20unexpected%20medical%20bills.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Funderstanding-the-no-surprises-act%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENo%20Surprises%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20went%20into%20effect%20in%202022%2C%20is%20supposed%20to%20keep%20patients%20from%20getting%20stuck%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F4-surprising-medical-costs-how-to-avoid-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurprise%20bill%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20they%20inadvertently%20receive%20care%20from%20an%20out-of-network%20doctor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Adams%20said%20patients%20should%20have%20a%20better%20sense%20of%20what%20they'll%20be%20required%20to%20pay%20ahead%20of%20getting%20care%20and%20more%20clarity%20about%20their%20options%20when%20they%20get%20a%20big%20bill.%20Furthermore%2C%20he%20said%20patients%20shouldn't%20face%20drastically%20different%20costs%20for%20the%20same%20care%20at%20different%20facilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20so%20scared%20of%20these%20bills%20due%20to%20lack%20of%20transparency.%20They%20actually%20just%20don't%20go%20in%20at%20all%20until%20it%20truly%20does%20become%20an%20emergency%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ER%20visit%20isn't%20Adams'%20first%20brush%20with%20an%20unexpected%20bill%2C%20and%20he%20fears%20it%20won't%20be%20the%20last.%20He%20said%20the%20Mayo%20Clinic's%20billing%20department%20warned%20him%20that%20he%20might%20receive%20another%20bill%20for%20his%20ambulance%20ride%20to%20the%20hospital.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20fortunate%20enough%20to%20be%20able%20to%20swing%20these%20bills%20if%20he%20has%20to%2C%20he%20said.%20That's%20not%20the%20case%20for%20many%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20many%20flaws%20in%20the%20system%20that%20would've%20caused%20other%20individuals%20to%20have%20gone%20into%20debt%2C%20have%20their%20credit%20ruined%2C%20or%20have%20to%20make%20choices%20about%20things%20they%20needed%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Adams%20said.%20%26quot%3BI've%20got%20three%20high%20schoolers%2C%20two%20kids%20heading%20to%20college.%20If%20I%20wasn't%20in%20my%20income%20bracket%2C%20I%20might%20be%20making%20a%20choice%20as%20to%20whether%20or%20not%20to%20pay%20my%20medical%20bill%20or%20to%20pay%20my%20kid's%20tuition.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-surgeon-general-medical-bill-shows-broken-healthcare-system-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709065751000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ddf660ce7f1785b2e42370%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-surgeon-general-medical-bill-shows-broken-healthcare-system-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Former%20US%20Surgeon%20General%20Jerome%20Adams%20said%20he%20got%20a%20%245%2C000%20bill%20for%20a%20recent%20ER%20visit%2C%20highlighting%20big%20problems%20with%20the%20US%20healthcare%20system.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22slivingston%40businessinsider.com%20(Shelby%20Livingston)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A32%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-surgeon-general-medical-bill-shows-broken-healthcare-system-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22OpenAI%20says%20New%20York%20Times%20'paid%20someone%20to%20hack%20OpenAI's%20products'%20in%20federal%20court%20filing%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225441%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22OpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%20speaks%20during%20the%20OpenAI%20DevDay%20event%20on%20November%206%2C%202023%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20California.%20(Photo%20by%20Justin%20Sullivan%2FGetty%20Images)%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6557fdb322cf74a57399c7d7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223825%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%20speaks%20during%20the%20OpenAI%20DevDay%20event%20on%20November%206%2C%202023%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20California.%3Cp%3EJustin%20Sullivan%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EOpenAI%20alleged%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20hired%20someone%20to%20%26quot%3Bhack%26quot%3B%20its%20platforms.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Times%20sued%20OpenAI%20and%20Microsoft%20in%20December%20for%20copyright%20infringement.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOpenAI%20also%20alleges%20that%20the%20Times%20gamed%20its%20platforms%20to%20generate%20deceptive%20evidence%20for%20its%20case.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20The%20New%20York%20Times'%20lawsuit%20against%20OpenAI%2C%20the%20artificial%20intelligence%20company%20is%20clapping%20back%2C%20saying%20in%20a%20new%20federal%20court%20filing%20that%20the%20Times%20hired%20someone%20to%20%26quot%3Bhack%26quot%3B%20OpenAI%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20truth%2C%20which%20will%20come%20out%20in%20the%20course%20of%20this%20case%2C%20is%20that%20the%20Times%20paid%20someone%20to%20hack%20OpenAI's%20products%2C%26quot%3B%20OpenAI's%20lawyers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffingfx.thomsonreuters.com%2Fgfx%2Flegaldocs%2Fbyvrkxbmgpe%2FOPENAI%2520MICROSOFT%2520NEW%2520YORK%2520TIMES%2520mtd.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%20in%20a%20motion%20filed%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Manhattan%20federal%20court%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20new%20filing%2C%20OpenAI%20is%20asking%20the%20judge%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20overarching%20lawsuit%20to%20dismiss%2C%20in%20full%20or%20in%20part%2C%20four%20of%20the%20six%20counts%20the%20Times%20leveled%20against%20OpenAI%20in%20its%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnyt-sues-open-ai-microsoft-alleging-trained-chatgpt-off-content-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETimes%20first%20sued%20OpenAI%20and%20Microsoft%3C%2Fa%3E%20back%20in%20December%2C%20alleging%20that%20both%20companies%20illegally%20used%20Times%20articles%20to%20train%20their%20AI%20chatbots%20to%20create%20products%20that%20compete%20with%20them%2C%20amounting%20to%20copyright%20infringement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20the%20Times%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24443737-httpsecfnysduscourtsgovcgi-binshow_tem%5B%E2%80%A6%5D0907598186089796pdftypeapplicationpdf%3Fresponsive%3D1%26title%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealleged%20in%20its%20original%20complaint%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20OpenAI's%20GPT-4%20spat%20out%20%26quot%3Bnear-verbatim%20copies%26quot%3B%20of%20Times%20articles%20when%20prompted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20OpenAI's%20attorneys%20wrote%20in%20Monday's%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emotion%20that%20the%20way%20the%20Times%20got%20the%20AI%20platform%20to%20show%20seemingly%20plagiarized%20responses%20was%20not%20in%20line%20with%20its%20own%20%26quot%3Bfamously%20rigorous%20journalistic%20standards.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20did%20the%20Times%20pay%20someone%20to%20%26quot%3Bhack%26quot%3B%20OpenAI's%20products%2C%20the%20filing%20alleges%2C%20but%20it%20also%20gamed%20the%20system%20to%20produce%20misleading%20evidence%20for%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20took%20them%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20attempts%20to%20generate%20the%20highly%20anomalous%20results%26quot%3B%20outlined%20in%20the%20Times'%20complaint%2C%20OpenAI's%20filing%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20were%20able%20to%20do%20so%20only%20by%20targeting%20and%20exploiting%20a%20bug%20(which%20OpenAI%20has%20committed%20to%20addressing)%20by%20using%20deceptive%20prompts%20that%20blatantly%20violate%20OpenAI's%20terms%20of%20use%2C%26quot%3B%20OpenAI's%20lawyers%20wrote%20in%20the%20filing.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20even%20then%2C%20they%20had%20to%20feed%20the%20tool%20portions%20of%20the%20very%20articles%20they%20sought%20to%20elicit%20verbatim%20passages%20of%2C%20virtually%20all%20of%20which%20already%20appear%20on%20multiple%20public%20websites.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNormal%20people%20do%20not%20use%20OpenAI's%20products%20in%20this%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20filing%20continues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20does%20not%20specifically%20name%20the%20Times'%20%26quot%3Bhired%20gun%2C%26quot%3B%20nor%20does%20it%20provide%20many%20details%20backing%20up%20its%20accusation%20%E2%80%94%20it%20merely%20suggests%20that%20the%20media%20company%20paid%20an%20%26quot%3Bagent%26quot%3B%20to%20create%20%26quot%3Bcontrived%20attacks%26quot%3B%20against%20OpenAI's%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20goes%20on%20to%20argue%20that%20the%20Times%20does%20not%20have%20ownership%20of%20facts%20and%20language%2C%20which%20it%20says%20are%20at%20the%20core%20of%20what%20its%20platforms%20are%20being%20trained%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Times's%20lawsuit%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-legal-trouble-bad-news-ai-industry-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejust%20one%20of%20many%20suits%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20have%20been%20lodged%20against%20OpenAI%20and%20other%20tech%20companies%20in%20recent%20months.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgame-of-thrones-author-sues-chatgpt-openai-copyright-infringement-lawsuit-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20number%20of%20writers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20George%20R.%20R.%20Martin%2C%20Sarah%20Silverman%2C%20John%20Grisham%2C%20and%20thousands%20of%20others%20have%20piled%20on%20to%20sue%20the%20company%20for%20copyright%20infringement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAttorneys%20for%20The%20N