19fa87ac%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222252%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWe%20don't%20like%20having%20a%20tight%20schedule%20on%20vacation.%20%3Cp%3EKristeen%20Cherney%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20setting%20sail%2C%20each%20group%20is%20supposed%20to%20select%20a%20dining%20time%20to%20stick%20with%20for%20every%20evening%20of%20the%20cruise.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20similar%20to%20how%20we%20eat%20at%20a%20scheduled%20time%20each%20night%20based%20on%20school%2C%20work%2C%20and%20extracurricular%20activities%20when%20we're%20not%20on%20vacation.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20since%20our%20day-to-day%20lives%20are%20already%20so%20planned%2C%20the%20last%20thing%20we%20want%20is%20a%20set%20dinnertime%20on%20our%20cruise.%20With%20the%20exception%20of%20seeing%20a%20show%20or%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-i-never-buy-on-a-cruise-frequent-traveler-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Egoing%20on%20an%20excursion%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20we%20avoid%20strict%20schedules%20as%20much%20as%20possible%20on%20vacation.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPlus%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20day%20and%20any%20other%20activities%20we're%20interested%20in%2C%20we%20may%20not%20even%20want%20to%20eat%20dinner%20at%20the%20same%20time%20each%20night.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20its%20credit%2C%20Royal%20Caribbean%20offers%20a%20My%20Time%20Dining%20option%2C%20where%20guests%20may%20show%20up%20to%20eat%20in%20the%20main%20dining%20room%20at%20any%20time%20during%20meal%20hours%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3Eif%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%20there's%20availability.%20This%20hasn't%20been%20enough%20to%20entice%20us%20to%20go%2C%20though.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20also%20prefer%20having%20flexible%20food%20choices%20and%20small%20bites%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI've%20heard%20Royal%20Caribbean's%20main%20dining%20menu%20is%20quite%20good.%20However%2C%20our%20family%20prefers%20to%20have%20more%20flexible%20food%20choices%2C%20particularly%20since%20one%20of%20us%20has%20sensory%20issues%20with%20food.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20we%20tend%20to%20stay%20pretty%20active%20on%20the%20cruise%2C%20we'd%20also%20rather%20eat%20small%20bites%20throughout%20the%20day%20instead%20of%20a%20multicourse%20dinner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20need%20for%20us%20to%20cause%20discomfort%20in%20the%20dining%20room%20and%20%3Cspan%3Etry%20to%20force%20a%20drawn-out%20dinner%20of%20multiple%20courses%20we%20don't%20even%20want%20to%20have.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFortunately%2C%20most%20Royal%20Caribbean%20ships%20have%20plenty%20of%20options%20for%20a%20quick%20bite.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESometimes%20we'll%20hit%20up%20the%20Windjammer%20Buffet%20for%20dinner%20or%20dessert%20(or%20both)%20or%20get%20pizza%20from%20Sorrento's%20Pizza.%20If%20we%20crave%20an%20early%20dinner%2C%20we%20might%20get%20a%20Cuban%20panini%20from%20the%20ship's%20Park%20Caf%C3%A9%20deli%20or%20a%20hot%20dog%20from%20Boardwalk%20Dog%20House.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOther%20times%2C%20we'll%20dine%20at%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-its-like-eating-disney-wish-adult-restaurant-palo-steakhouse-photos-2022%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Especialty%20sit-down%20restauran%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Et%20that%20costs%20extra.%20Even%20so%2C%20that's%20just%20one%20meal%20of%20our%20cruise%20%E2%80%94%20not%20a%20nightly%20commitment%20to%20the%20main%20dining%20room.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20don't%20mess%20with%20formal%20wear%20and%20staged%20photos%2C%20either%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Empty%20deck%20on%20Royal%20Caribbean%20cruise%20%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65de2c7090413ab8e1d72f44%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222252%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20hours%20before%20formal%20nights%20are%20the%20best%20time%20to%20visit%20the%20pool.%3Cp%3EKristeen%20Cherney%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20are%20two%20formal%20nights%20on%20our%20typical%20seven-night%20cruises.%20%3C%2Fspan%3EFor%20these%20special%20occasions%2C%20most%20guests%20get%20dolled%20up%20and%20have%20the%20chance%20to%20pose%20for%20professional%20photos.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20getting%20ready%20for%20a%20formal%20night%20could%20take%20my%20family%20hours.%20%3Cspan%3EAlthough%20we%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-rooms-windows-balconies-not-worth-it-frequent-cruiser-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ealways%20book%20a%20balcony%20room%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20with%20a%20decent%20amount%20of%20space%2C%20we%20still%20have%20to%20share%20just%20one%20bathroom%20and%20limited%20counter%20space.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlso%2C%20the%20last%20thing%20we%20want%20to%20worry%20about%20on%20vacation%20is%20carefully%20packing%20and%20finding%20a%20place%20to%20hang%20fancy%20clothes%20so%20they%20won't%20get%20wrinkled.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe've%20also%20found%20that%20skipping%20formal%20night%20means%20we%20get%20more%20of%20the%20ship%20to%20ourselves.%20On%20these%20nights%2C%20the%20ship's%20main%20pool%20usually%20clears%20out%20midafternoon%20as%20people%20rush%20to%20their%20cabins%20to%20get%20ready%2C%20meaning%20there's%20more%20room%20for%20us.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20also%20really%20%3C%2Fspan%3Edon't%20%3Cspan%3Efeel%20like%20we're%20missing%20out.%20On%20our%20way%20to%20grab%20pizza%20on%20formal%20nights%2C%20we've%20passed%20parents%20begging%20crying%20children%20to%20pose%20for%20an%20awkwardly%20staged%20photograph%20in%20clothing%20I'm%20certain%20is%20uncomfortable%20for%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20we've%20seen%20many%20folks%20in%20suits%20and%20gowns%20leaving%20the%20main%20dining%20room%20to%20grab%20slices%20of%20pizza%20%E2%80%A6%20which%20makes%20us%20question%20if%20the%20special%20nights%20are%20all%20they're%20cracked%20up%20to%20be%20anyway.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-eating-main-dining-room-not-worth-it-royal-caribbean%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709065078000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65de4352ce7f1785b2e44b69%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-eating-main-dining-room-not-worth-it-royal-caribbean%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Kristeen%20Cherney)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-eating-main-dining-room-not-worth-it-royal-caribbean%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Wait.%20Why%20is%20Reddit%20losing%20so%20much%20money%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Reddit%20logo%20on%20a%20cell%20phone%20with%20images%20of%20dollar%20bill%20in%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65de226090413ab8e1d72997%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223320%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EReddit%20is%20losing%20money%2C%20it%20reports%20in%20its%20IPO%20documents.%20But%20why%3F%20It's%20at%20least%20partly%20because%20of%20R%26amp%3BD%20spending.%3Cp%3ESOPA%20Images%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-ipo-redditors-stock-wallstreetbets-meme-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReddit%20is%20going%20public%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20lost%20nearly%20%2491%20million%20last%20year%2C%20the%20company%20said%20in%20its%20newly%20filed%20IPO%20documents.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhy's%20it%20losing%20so%20much%3F%20It's%20at%20least%20partly%20because%20it's%20spending%20so%20much%20on%20R%26amp%3BD.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-ipo-shares-loyal-users-ai-steve-huffman-sam-altman-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReddit%20is%20going%20public%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20a%20time-tested%20business%20model%20pioneered%20by%20the%20likes%20of%20Facebook%20and%20Twitter%3A%20Get%20people%20to%20give%20you%20content%2C%20for%20free%2C%20and%20sell%20ads%20on%20that%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20why%20is%20it%20losing%20so%20much%20money%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthousands-reddit-users-could-buy-stock-in-ipo-report-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReddit's%20newly%20filed%20IPO%20documents%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20company%20generated%20%24804%20million%20in%20revenue%20and%20lost%20nearly%20%2491%20million.%20That's%20better%20than%20the%20year%20before%2C%20when%20it%20lost%20%24159%20million%20on%20on%20revenue%20of%20%24667%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20still%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20to%20lose%20selling%20a%20free%20product.%20Right%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20unusual%20for%20tech%20companies%20to%20lose%20money%20as%20they're%20going%20public.%20And%20when%20they%20do%2C%20the%20rationale%20is%20usually%20that%20these%20are%20young%2C%20fast-growing%20businesses%2C%20and%20investors%20are%20getting%20a%20chance%20to%20get%20in%20early.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Reddit%20is%20no%20baby%3A%20It%20started%20nearly%20two%20decades%20ago%2C%20in%202005.%20Cond%C3%A9%20Nast%2C%20the%20magazine%20giant%2C%20bought%20it%20in%202006%20and%20spun%20it%20out%20as%20a%20stand-alone%20company%20in%202011.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit%20kind%20of%20anticipates%20this%20critique%20in%20its%20investor%20docs%2C%20and%20argues%20that%20it%20didn't%20really%20start%20operating%20as%20a%20serious%20business%20until%202018%20when%20it%20finally%20started%20%26quot%3Bmeaningful%20monetization%20efforts%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20that%20is%2C%20trying%20to%20make%20money%20for%20real.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that's%20still%20six%20years%20ago.%20What%20has%20Reddit%20been%20doing%20since%20then%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20big%2C%20obvious%20answer%3A%20It%20has%20been%20hiring%20a%20lot%20of%20engineers%20and%20spending%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20on%20their%20salaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Reddit%20CEO%20Steve%20Huffman%20speaks%20at%20a%20conference%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65de1a6a90413ab8e1d724e6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EReddit%20CEO%20Steve%20Huffman's%20compensation%20is%20not%20included%20in%20the%20company's%20research%20and%20development%20spending.%3Cp%3EGreg%20Doherty%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20Reddit's%20spending%20on%20research%20and%20development%20%E2%80%94%20which%20it%20says%20is%20money%20spent%20primarily%20on%20%26quot%3Bengineers%20and%20other%20employees%20engaged%20in%20the%20research%2C%20design%2C%20and%20development%20of%20new%20and%20existing%20products%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20totaled%20%24439%20million%2C%20an%20eye-popping%2055%25%20of%20its%20revenue.%20(Note%3A%20There%20are%20some%20dumb%20stories%20floating%20out%20there%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-cofounder-firm-was-more-like-homework-assignment-than-business-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReddit%20CEO%20Steve%20Huffman%3C%2Fa%3E%20getting%20paid%20%24193%20million%20last%20year.%20You%20can%20ignore%20those%20in%20general%20since%20they%20are%20really%20about%20stock%20and%20options%20awards%20with%20a%20long%20vesting%20period.%20And%20you%20can%20specifically%20ignore%20them%20for%20this%20story%20since%20those%20costs%20aren't%20included%20in%20the%20R%26amp%3BD%20totals.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20comparison%3A%20When%20Facebook%20went%20public%20in%202012%2C%20R%26amp%3BD%20was%2010%25%20of%20its%20revenue.%20Last%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcharts-meta-metaverse-spending-losses-reality-labs-vr-mark-zuckerberg-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhen%20it%20was%20building%20things%20like%20virtual%20reality%20goggles%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20that%20number%20had%20bumped%20up%20to%2029%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Twitter%20went%20public%20in%202013%2C%20R%26amp%3BD%20was%2044%25%20of%20revenue.%20And%20at%20the%20end%20of%202021%2C%20the%20last%20year%20it%20filed%20a%20public%20statement%20before%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdid-elon-musk-buy-twitter-acquisition-details%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%20bought%20the%20company%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20that%20number%20was%20down%20to%2025%25.%20Bear%20in%20mind%20this%20was%20a%20company%20that%20both%20Musk%20%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%20Twitter%20management%20thought%20was%20overstaffed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20numbers%20puzzle%20me.%20Reddit%20works%20great%20for%20the%20people%20who%20love%20it%2C%20and%20there%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20them.%20But%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20it%20works%20great%20is%20that%20it's%20a%20pretty%20bare-bones%20product%20that%20does%20what%20it's%20supposed%20to%3A%20It%20lets%20people%20post%20something%20they're%20interested%20in%20and%20then%20lets%20other%20people%20comment%20about%20it.%20That's%20it.%20That's%20the%20whole%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EReddit%20is%20adding%20users%20%E2%80%94%20a%20bright%20spot%20with%20caveats%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20am%20I%20missing%3F%20I%20asked%20Reddit%20comms%20for%20comment%20but%20they%20declined%2C%20citing%20the%20company's%20quiet%20period%20before%20the%20IPO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20argument%20I%20can%20make%20in%20their%20defense%20is%20that%20Reddit%20is%20still%20adding%20a%20lot%20of%20users%20and%20that%20more%20users%20equals%20more%20ad%20money.%20(Of%20note%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F2%2F23%2F24080516%2Freddit-biggest-risk-is-google%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Verge's%20Alex%20Heath%3C%2Fa%3E%20argues%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20Reddit's%20recent%20growth%20has%20come%20from%20a%20surge%20of%20Google%20traffic.%20And%20as%20any%20digital%20media%20company%20can%20tell%20you%20%E2%80%94%20traffic%20surges%20from%20platforms%20can%20also%20get%20shut%20off%2C%20very%20quickly.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%20there's%20more%20money%20coming%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-train-ai-model-crazy-subreddit-posts-reddit-licensing-deal-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI-training%20data%20deal%20it%20did%20with%20Google%3C%2Fa%3E%20(Hey!%20Google%20again!).%20And%20that%20money%20is%20basically%20cost-free%2C%20so%20that's%20going%20to%20make%20the%20margins%20look%20better%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIs%20that%20enough%20to%20make%20investors%20comfortable%20with%20a%20theoretical%20%245%20billion%20valuation%3F%20Am%20I%20missing%20something%3F%20Feel%20free%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Apkafka%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemail%20me%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20let%20me%20know.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-reddit-loses-money-ipo-research-development-revenue-2024-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709064695000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65de227e6080194819fa829b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-reddit-loses-mo